      "widgets_values": [
        "MERGE #1 — Towers/Spires (foreground) + Relief Mesh (background)\n\nScenario: a tall structure (church spire, tower, high-rise) whose\nfull height is the point of the shot. AtlasDeriveWalls/azimuth_walls\nwould truncate it at the first non-vertical-normal point (it clips\nsloped roofs/spires) — AtlasDeriveTowersSpires instead extrudes to the\nreal image-space silhouette top (Hoiem/Efros/Hebert photo pop-up\nbillboard-cutout technique), so the spire reads at its true height.\n\n1. Node 4 (foreground) — AtlasDeriveTowersSpires on the tower/spire.\n2. Node 5 (background) — AtlasDeriveReliefMesh for everything else\n   (surrounding rooftops, sky-adjacent terrain) that a flat wall\n   extrusion wouldn't represent well.\n3. Node 6 — AtlasMergeGeometry combines them; solve_a (the tower)\n   provides the merged camera. Both branches come from the same\n   upstream solve/depth, so they already share one.\n\nHit 📽 Project in the viewport to see the full-height spire and the\nbackground terrain textured from the recovered camera together."
      ]
    }
